  "business_context": "Grant records track institutional funding awards — the structured, formalized cousin of individual donations. Where a Donation is typically a single-event gift, a Grant is a multi-stage relationship with a funder: writing the proposal, submission, review period, award decision, award letter signing, payment installments, periodic progress reports, outcomes reporting, and closeout. Each stage may have its own deadlines and stakeholders. Restricted-use is the defining characteristic — grant funds typically must be spent on specific programs, with reporting requirements that document compliance. NPSP has a Grant Record Type on Opportunity (and a Grant Deadline / Deliverable concept for tracking reporting deadlines). CiviCRM has a Grants extension. Bloomerang doesn't have first-class grants but accommodates them via Transaction with grant-specific custom fields and Funds. When interviewing clients, surface \"Grant\" by asking whether they receive funding from foundations or government bodies, whether they need to track proposal-to-award workflows separately from donations, and whether they have grant reporting / compliance requirements that need deadline tracking.",
  "catalog_id": "grant",
  "common_synonyms": [
    "Foundation Grant",
    "Government Grant",
    "Corporate Grant",
    "Sponsorship",
    "Award"
  ],
